{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9603", "repo": "rails", "body": "I thought `find_or_*_by` methods were removed in favor of `where(...).first_or_*` but I see that they still do exist. As I said, it makes sense to use verb there, find_or_new_by doesn't sound right. I would leave it as is unless you have other ideas.\r\n\r\nDo we want to deprecate and remove first_and_initialize or have it as an alias? I'm fine with both options.", "_id": {"$oid": "5237e816bd3543c15100967f"}, "issue_id": 9603, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/14697145", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9603#issuecomment-14697145", "updated_at": "2013-03-11T04:20:56Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/semaperepelitsa/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/semaperepelitsa/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/semaperepelitsa/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/semaperepelitsa/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/semaperepelitsa", "login": "semaperepelitsa", "gravatar_id": "607564f1a15f1899c71b4a9fdfc33ac2", "html_url": "https://github.com/semaperepelitsa", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/semaperepelitsa/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/semaperepelitsa/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/semaperepelitsa/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/607564f1a15f1899c71b4a9fdfc33ac2?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fdfaa83a66fe63d7e6e744189e2594a31.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/semaperepelitsa/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 347921, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/semaperepelitsa/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-03-11T04:20:56Z", "id": 14697145, "owner": "rails"}
